Re: Translation Help
by becki_kanou » Sat 07.30.2011 6:45 pm If neither you nor your tattoo artist can read Japanese, the chance of the characters coming out badly done, sideways, mirrored, upside-down or just plain ugly is quite high. Take a gander at Hanzi Smatter before you go through with your plan.That said the characters you posted are correct, if in an ugly font, although 勇 looks kind of lopsided. Proceed with caution, or get a tattoo in a language you can actually read.
そうだ、嬉しいんだ、生きる喜び！
例え胸の傷が痛んでも。
